Claude Code Task: Build codeutils.de Hub Landing Page
Project Overview
Create a modern, clean developer tools hub landing page for codeutils.de - a gallery-style page that immediately shows the tools without a hero section.
Tech Stack

Static HTML/CSS/JS (keep it simple, fast-loading)
Tailwind CSS via CDN (or vanilla CSS if preferred)
Deploy-ready for Coolify on Hetzner
No framework needed - pure static site

Design Approach

No hero section - visitors should immediately see the tools
Gallery/card style layout with screenshots
Clean, minimal header with just logo/brand
Tools are the main focus

Structure
1. Minimal Header

Logo: "codeutils.de"
Small tagline underneath: "Free developer tools. No ads. No tracking."

2. Tools Gallery (Main Content)
Large cards with:

Screenshot of the tool (prominent, takes most of card space)
Tool name
One-line description
"Open Tool" button
Link opens in new tab

Current tools:
ToolURLDescriptionBase64 Decoder/Encoderhttps://www.base64decoder.deEncode and decode Base64 strings instantlyJSON Formatterhttps://www.jsonformat.deFormat, validate and beautify JSON data
Screenshots needed:

Take screenshots of both tools (or use placeholder images initially)
Recommended size: 16:9 aspect ratio, ~800x450px
Store in /images/screenshots/

3. Coming Soon Section (smaller cards, grayed out)

URL Encoder/Decoder
JWT Decoder
UUID Generator
Timestamp Converter
Regex Tester
YAML ↔ JSON Converter

4. Minimal Footer

"Built by a developer, for developers"
"All tools run client-side - your data stays private"
Impressum link (German legal requirement)
Copyright

Design Requirements

Dark mode by default
Mobile responsive (cards stack on mobile)
Fast loading
Clean, professional look
Cards should have subtle hover effects
Screenshots should have subtle border/shadow

Data Structure
Make tools configurable via JS array for easy additions:
javascriptconst tools = [
  {
    name: "Base64 Decoder/Encoder",
    url: "https://www.base64decoder.de",
    description: "Encode and decode Base64 strings instantly",
    screenshot: "/images/screenshots/base64decoder.png",
    active: true
  },
  {
    name: "JSON Formatter", 
    url: "https://www.jsonformat.de",
    description: "Format, validate and beautify JSON data",
    screenshot: "/images/screenshots/jsonformat.png",
    active: true
  },
  {
    name: "URL Encoder/Decoder",
    url: "#",
    description: "Encode and decode URLs",
    screenshot: null,
    active: false // coming soon
  }
  // ... more tools
];
```

